(169,1,'2024-02-29 07:06:30','2024-02-29 07:06:30','<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is Lorem Ipsum?</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Lorem Ipsum</strong>&nbsp;is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry\'s standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It was popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containing Lorem Ipsum passages, and more recently with desktop publishing software like Aldus PageMaker including versions of Lorem Ipsum.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why do we use it?</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when looking at its layout. The point of using Lorem Ipsum is that it has a more-or-less normal distribution of letters, as opposed to using \'Content here, content here\', making it look like readable English. Many desktop publishing packages and web page editors now use Lorem Ipsum as their default model text, and a search for \'lorem ipsum\' will uncover many web sites still in their infancy. Various versions have evolved over the years, sometimes by accident, sometimes on purpose (injected humour and the like).</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Where does it come from?</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Contrary to popular belief, Lorem Ipsum is not simply random text. It has roots in a piece of classical Latin literature from 45 BC, making it over 2000 years old. Richard McClintock, a Latin professor at Hampden-Sydney College in Virginia, looked up one of the more obscure Latin words, consectetur, from a Lorem Ipsum passage, and going through the cites of the word in classical literature, discovered the undoubtable source. Lorem Ipsum comes from sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 of \"de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum\" (The Extremes of Good and Evil) by Cicero, written in 45 BC. This book is a treatise on the theory of ethics, very popular during the Renaissance. The first line of Lorem Ipsum, \"Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet..\", comes from a line in section 1.10.32.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>The standard chunk of Lorem Ipsum used since the 1500s is reproduced below for those interested. Sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 from \"de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum\" by Cicero are also reproduced in their exact original form, accompanied by English versions from the 1914 translation by H. Rackham.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Where can I get some?</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>There are many variations of passages of Lorem Ipsum available, but the majority have suffered alteration in some form, by injected humour, or randomised words which don\'t look even slightly believable. If you are going to use a passage of Lorem Ipsum, you need to be sure there isn\'t anything embarrassing hidden in the middle of text. All the Lorem Ipsum generators on the Internet tend to repeat predefined chunks as necessary, making this the first true generator on the Internet. It uses a dictionary of over 200 Latin words, combined with a handful of model sentence structures, to generate Lorem Ipsum which looks reasonable. The generated Lorem Ipsum is therefore always free from repetition, injected humour, or non-characteristic words etc.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Budget Bites','','inherit','closed','closed','','54-revision-v1','','','2024-02-29 07:06:30','2024-02-29 07:06:30','',54,'http://localwww.krishmish.com/?p=169',0,'revision','',0),
(171,1,'2024-02-29 07:29:32','2024-02-29 07:29:32','<div class=\"BL3dva\">\r\n<div class=\"OSxNQL\">\r\n<div class=\"OFA52E\">\r\n<div class=\"cD_92h UitnHM\" tabindex=\"-1\" data-hook=\"post-title\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"nLG8d5\" data-hook=\"post-description\"><article class=\"blog-post-page-font\">\r\n<div class=\"post-content__body stSKMK\">\r\n<div class=\"moHCnT\">\r\n<div class=\"moHCnT\">\r\n<div class=\"fTEXDR A2sIZ4 QEEfz0\" data-rce-version=\"9.17.7\">\r\n<div class=\"Bteo4\" dir=\"ltr\" data-id=\"content-viewer\">\r\n<div class=\"_8Tyov\" data-query=\"container\">\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block-first\"></div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block-first\">Biryani, a culinary masterpiece that hails from the Indian subcontinent, is known for its delightful blend of fragrant spices and flavorful ingredients. Traditionally biryani is prepared with meat or chicken and you love the fragrance coming from biryani but can’t indulge it because it is non-vegetarian while your friends enjoy it to the utmost. Don’t worry Charcoal Eats won’t keep you deprived of biryani whether you are vegetarian or non-vegetarian. We have lots of options for you to choose from. Let’s explore the different types of vegetarian biryani recipes that will tantalize your taste buds and satisfy your soul.</div>\r\n<div class=\"RMtIP\">\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<div id=\"viewer-zbric3234\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\"> </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block2\"></div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h2 id=\"viewer-twh4m3235\" class=\"Y6Mj6 XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">What is Vegetarian Biryani?</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block3\"></div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-2sjvx3237\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">If you say <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://www.charcoaleats.com/hyderabadi-veg-biryani\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">vegetarian Biryani</a> in front of a non-vegetarian lover they will definitely laugh but why should non-vegetarians have all the fun? Vegetarian biryani is especially made for vegetarians who love the aroma and flavor of biryani but with the fear of indulging meat, they don’t dare to eat it. Now, several biryani restaurants are taking vegetarian urges towards the biryani and offering vegetarian biryani at their restaurants. One of them is <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://www.charcoaleats.com/menu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">Charcoal Eats </a>which has a variety of vegetarian biryani recipes and options to choose from. </span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h2 id=\"viewer-8lslk3244\" class=\"Y6Mj6 XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Explore Various Vegetarian Biryani Recipes </span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-6fzq63246\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">There are a vast variety of vegetarian biryani recipes let’s explore some of them: </span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-5hg5i3249\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Vegetable Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-2j3rp3251\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">It is a medley of colorful vegetables like carrots, peas, beans, and bell peppers cooked with fragrant basmati rice and aromatic spices. This is the most classic and widely loved vegetarian biryani.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-5amdk3254\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Tofu Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-eg4ib3256\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">For those who prefer plant-based protein, tofu biryani is a delightful choice, with tofu cut into cubes absorbing the fragrant spices and creating a delightful fusion of flavors.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-l9wn83259\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Mushroom Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-1cn043261\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Mushrooms bring an earthy and meaty texture to the dish. Those who can’t experience the taste of meat can enjoy mushroom biryani to satisfy their cravings. Mushrooms absorb the rich biryani flavors beautifully, making it a favorite among mushroom lovers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-b29da3264\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Paneer Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-rfanr3266\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">For people who love paneer, this biryani recipe is just for them. Cut paneer into small cubes, marinate them with species and deep fry them for once. Then layer it with rice, creating a biryani that\'s rich, indulgent, and perfect for paneer lovers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-98lcj3269\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Jackfruit Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-cs0i43271\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Unripe jackfruit, known as \"kathal\" in India, hits the right spot in texture and tastes like chicken. It\'s a perfect versatile and nutritious meat substitute. When spiced and cooked with rice, it creates a unique biryani with a satisfying texture.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-czhx03274\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Soy Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-vvv4i3276\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Under a lot of vegetable biryani varieties, soy biryani holds a different place. Soy chunks or granules are used to mimic the texture of meat, and when combined with spices and rice, it results in a protein-packed and delicious biryani.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-hqgbu3280\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Hyderabadi Mirchi Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-dbecf3282\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Those who love to spice things up should try this biryani which features green chilies as the star ingredient, giving it a spicy kick. It\'s an excellent choice for those who enjoy bold flavors, aroma and are vegetarian. </span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-9blgv3285\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Cauliflower Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-19jpi3287\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Into the types of veg biryani lies the cauliflower biryani which is cooked with rice and spices to create a biryani that\'s both fragrant and filling. The mild flavor of cauliflower pairs well with the biryani\'s spices satisfying the taste buds of vegetarians. </span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-7p8iq3290\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Brinjal (Eggplant) Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-q8ojl3292\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Eggplant biryani is on a different level when it comes to vegetarian biryani recipe. Brinjal  is marinated and roasted before being added to the biryani, lending a smoky and rich flavor to this biryani vegetarian variation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-jsjhp3295\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Kofta Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-d64bl3297\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Lauki or paneer koftas are simmered in a spiced tomato gravy and then layered with rice, creating a biryani that\'s rich and indulgent. Perfect to come under vegetable biryani varieties. </span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-bpaa43300\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Spinach and Potato Biryani</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-qdsjh3302\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">This <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1o-uHYnjW8BVHsQBAulZJQ7U940fQHZqW5bbj84Vtjqw/edit\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">healthy biryani recipe</a> combines the earthy flavors of potatoes with the healthful goodness of spinach, resulting in a wholesome and comforting meal. Make sure to make it in the winter season as it was totally worth it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p id=\"viewer-d9vkh3308\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Vegetarian biryanis showcase the incredible diversity of ingredients and flavors that the culinary world has to offer. Whether you\'re a fan of vegetables, mushrooms, paneer, or unique meat substitutes, there\'s a vegetarian biryani variety to suit your taste. These recipes prove that you don\'t need meat to enjoy the rich, aromatic, and satisfying experience of biryani. So, explore these vegetarian biryani recipes or <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://order.charcoaleats.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">order vegetarian biryani online</a> from <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://www.charcoaleats.com/menu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">Charcoal Eats</a> offering vibrant vegetarian biryanis, and enjoy it right from the comfort of your home. </span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block43\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block-last\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</article></div>\r\n<div class=\"BL3dva\">\r\n<div class=\"OSxNQL\">\r\n<div id=\"post-footer\" class=\"OFA52E jG7PL8\">\r\n<div class=\"ux83lW\" data-hook=\"post-main-actions-desktop\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Different Types of Vegetarian Biryani Recipes','','inherit','closed','closed','','170-revision-v1','','','2024-02-29 07:29:32','2024-02-29 07:29:32','',170,'http://localwww.krishmish.com/?p=171',0,'revision','',0),
(172,1,'2024-02-29 11:58:59','2024-02-29 11:58:59','<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-dd09e\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">India is a land of diverse flavors and culinary traditions. Here everyone likes kebabs, and it\'s very difficult to resist those succulent pieces of meat cooked in a variety of styles and seasonings, each with its own distinct flavor. From smoky tandoori kebabs to succulent seekh kebabs, there are various different types of kebabs in India. As India has a significant Mughal influence, it is home to some of the most delicious and various types of <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://www.charcoaleats.com/menu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">kebab</a>. In India every city offers a unique taste of kebab, let’s explore some unique flavors of kebab.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h2 id=\"viewer-64lt0\" class=\"Y6Mj6 XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">What is Kebab?</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-amd8t\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">First thing first let’s understand what is kebab. Kebabs are a popular Middle Eastern food made by mounting pieces of meat on a skewer and grilling it later. Well, Kebabs are considered to have originated in Turkey. The“kebab” in Turkish means “grilled meat.” The story behind the origin of kebab is that once Turkish soldiers were grilling chunks of freshly hunted animal meat skewed on swords on open fire. That’s how kebabs were invented. However, now it has become an essential part of the meal in Eastern and Asian households. With its interesting story of origin, kebabs come in different unique flavors as each city around the world holds its uniqueness in the food and technique they use to make that food. Let’s savor the flavor of various types of kebas.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-bnr7j\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Tandoori Chicken Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-l2uc\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Tandoori chicken kebabs are the epitome of smoky perfection. Marinated in a mixture of yogurt, spices, and a dash of citrus, the chicken is then cooked in a tandoor (clay oven) to achieve that distinct charred flavor. The result is tender, flavorful chicken with a beautiful reddish hue that\'s simply irresistible.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-6o44i\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Seekh Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-crv2\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Seekh kebabs are a staple at Indian barbecue gatherings. These cylindrical-shaped kebabs are made from minced meat (usually lamb or chicken) blended with aromatic spices and fresh herbs. The mixture is molded onto skewers and grilled until charred on the outside and juicy on the inside. Served with mint chutney and naan, seekh kebabs are a carnivore\'s dream.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-c4be6\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Galouti Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-sn8o\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Galouti kebabs are an example of the finesse of Indian cuisine. Originating from Lucknow, these kebabs are made from finely minced meat (traditionally lamb) that\'s marinated with an array of spices and then cooked to perfection. What makes them truly special is the addition of raw papaya, which acts as a natural tenderizer, giving the kebabs their legendary melt-in-the-mouth texture.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-d1nih\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Shami Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-7qnmr\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Making its way all the way from Hyderabad, Shami kebabs are the ideal choice for family gatherings. The Shami Kebab is made of a small patty of minced meat, chickpeas, and eggs, this holds the meat together. It tastes best with salad and lemon garnishing on the top.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-28oh1\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Paneer Tikka</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-86jkc\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Why should non-vegetarians should have all the fun? The paneer tikka kebab is a delightful alternative to the non-veg kebabs. Cubes of paneer are marinated in a mixture of yogurt, spices, and vibrant saffron, and then grilled to perfection. The result is a medley of flavors and textures - creamy paneer with a delightful smokiness.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-40t1o\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Chapli Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-8dab8\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">The chapli kebab is originated from the North-Western region of India. They are flat round in shape, typically made from minced meat (often beef or mutton) combined with a medley of spices, chopped onions, tomatoes, and fresh herbs. They\'re pan-fried to perfection, resulting in a crispy outer layer and a juicy interior.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-8o3hh\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Kalmi Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-c31o9\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">The Kalmi kebabs are a bit different from the other types of kebabs in India. The kalmi kebab is made with leg pieces (both chicken and meat). They are rich in flavor and creamy in texture as the masala used for making the Kalmi kebab cashews and cheese, which is later mixed with hung yogurt and other spices. It tastes so delicious that it will leave you crave for more.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block28\"></div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<div id=\"viewer-df5c5\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\"> </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block29\"></div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-4j7hs\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Malai Chicken Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-cd73m\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Malai chicken kebabs are a luscious treat that showcases the rich creaminess of Indian cuisine. Boneless chicken pieces are marinated in a mixture of cream, yogurt, cheese, and aromatic spices. The kebabs are then grilled creating a tender, moist, and smokey flavor.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block32\"></div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-bks62\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">These are just a few glimpses into the diverse and flavorful world of Indian kebabs. Whether you\'re a meat lover or a vegetarian, there are other types of kebab that will offer a vivid and vast taste of India\'s culinary heritage. <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://www.charcoaleats.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">Charcoal Eats</a> has got you covered with a variety of kebabs in India. If you are looking to <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://order.charcoaleats.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">order kebabs online</a>, order online from Charcoal Eats your preferred kebab. Enjoy an indulgent treat in comfort!</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>','Different Types Of Kebabs In India','','publish','open','open','','different-types-of-kebabs-in-india','','','2024-02-29 13:44:23','2024-02-29 13:44:23','',0,'http://localwww.krishmish.com/?p=172',0,'post','',0),
(173,1,'2024-02-29 11:58:02','2024-02-29 11:58:02','','kebab_desktop','','inherit','open','closed','','kebab_desktop','','','2024-02-29 11:58:16','2024-02-29 11:58:16','',172,'http://localwww.krishmish.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/kebab_desktop.webp',0,'attachment','image/webp',0),
(174,1,'2024-02-29 11:58:59','2024-02-29 11:58:59','<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-dd09e\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">India is a land of diverse flavors and culinary traditions. Here everyone likes kebabs, and it\'s very difficult to resist those succulent pieces of meat cooked in a variety of styles and seasonings, each with its own distinct flavor. From smoky tandoori kebabs to succulent seekh kebabs, there are various different types of kebabs in India. As India has a significant Mughal influence, it is home to some of the most delicious and various types of <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://www.charcoaleats.com/menu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">kebab</a>. In India every city offers a unique taste of kebab, let’s explore some unique flavors of kebab.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h2 id=\"viewer-64lt0\" class=\"Y6Mj6 XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">What is Kebab?</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-amd8t\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">First thing first let’s understand what is kebab. Kebabs are a popular Middle Eastern food made by mounting pieces of meat on a skewer and grilling it later. Well, Kebabs are considered to have originated in Turkey. The“kebab” in Turkish means “grilled meat.” The story behind the origin of kebab is that once Turkish soldiers were grilling chunks of freshly hunted animal meat skewed on swords on open fire. That’s how kebabs were invented. However, now it has become an essential part of the meal in Eastern and Asian households. With its interesting story of origin, kebabs come in different unique flavors as each city around the world holds its uniqueness in the food and technique they use to make that food. Let’s savor the flavor of various types of kebas.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-bnr7j\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Tandoori Chicken Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-l2uc\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Tandoori chicken kebabs are the epitome of smoky perfection. Marinated in a mixture of yogurt, spices, and a dash of citrus, the chicken is then cooked in a tandoor (clay oven) to achieve that distinct charred flavor. The result is tender, flavorful chicken with a beautiful reddish hue that\'s simply irresistible.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-6o44i\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Seekh Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-crv2\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Seekh kebabs are a staple at Indian barbecue gatherings. These cylindrical-shaped kebabs are made from minced meat (usually lamb or chicken) blended with aromatic spices and fresh herbs. The mixture is molded onto skewers and grilled until charred on the outside and juicy on the inside. Served with mint chutney and naan, seekh kebabs are a carnivore\'s dream.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-c4be6\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Galouti Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-sn8o\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Galouti kebabs are an example of the finesse of Indian cuisine. Originating from Lucknow, these kebabs are made from finely minced meat (traditionally lamb) that\'s marinated with an array of spices and then cooked to perfection. What makes them truly special is the addition of raw papaya, which acts as a natural tenderizer, giving the kebabs their legendary melt-in-the-mouth texture.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-d1nih\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Shami Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-7qnmr\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Making its way all the way from Hyderabad, Shami kebabs are the ideal choice for family gatherings. The Shami Kebab is made of a small patty of minced meat, chickpeas, and eggs, this holds the meat together. It tastes best with salad and lemon garnishing on the top.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-28oh1\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Paneer Tikka</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-86jkc\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Why should non-vegetarians should have all the fun? The paneer tikka kebab is a delightful alternative to the non-veg kebabs. Cubes of paneer are marinated in a mixture of yogurt, spices, and vibrant saffron, and then grilled to perfection. The result is a medley of flavors and textures - creamy paneer with a delightful smokiness.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-40t1o\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Chapli Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-8dab8\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">The chapli kebab is originated from the North-Western region of India. They are flat round in shape, typically made from minced meat (often beef or mutton) combined with a medley of spices, chopped onions, tomatoes, and fresh herbs. They\'re pan-fried to perfection, resulting in a crispy outer layer and a juicy interior.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-8o3hh\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Kalmi Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-c31o9\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">The Kalmi kebabs are a bit different from the other types of kebabs in India. The kalmi kebab is made with leg pieces (both chicken and meat). They are rich in flavor and creamy in texture as the masala used for making the Kalmi kebab cashews and cheese, which is later mixed with hung yogurt and other spices. It tastes so delicious that it will leave you crave for more.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block28\"></div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<div id=\"viewer-df5c5\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\"> </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block29\"></div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<h3 id=\"viewer-4j7hs\" class=\"IQ7kr XtK1R KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"hQoyd\">Malai Chicken Kebab</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-cd73m\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">Malai chicken kebabs are a luscious treat that showcases the rich creaminess of Indian cuisine. Boneless chicken pieces are marinated in a mixture of cream, yogurt, cheese, and aromatic spices. The kebabs are then grilled creating a tender, moist, and smokey flavor.</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div data-hook=\"rcv-block32\"></div>\r\n<div data-breakout=\"normal\">\r\n<p id=\"viewer-bks62\" class=\"_9-O5y h4vUg KNByY iPC6I TI-xX\"><span class=\"_1N6tE\">These are just a few glimpses into the diverse and flavorful world of Indian kebabs. Whether you\'re a meat lover or a vegetarian, there are other types of kebab that will offer a vivid and vast taste of India\'s culinary heritage. <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://www.charcoaleats.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">Charcoal Eats</a> has got you covered with a variety of kebabs in India. If you are looking to <a class=\"_37YHL hO7NK\" href=\"https://order.charcoaleats.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hook=\"WebLink\">order kebabs online</a>, order online from Charcoal Eats your preferred kebab. Enjoy an indulgent treat in comfort!</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>','Different Types Of Kebabs In India','','inherit','closed','closed','','172-revision-v1','','','2024-02-29 11:58:59','2024-02-29 11:58:59','',172,'http://localwww.krishmish.com/?p=174',0,'revision','',0),
